(8, 'the transformation of seo', '2016-04-12', 'SEO', '1460455162_evolution-seo-marketer-rebelute-1920-800x450.jpg', '', 0, '', 'Admin', 'In this blog you will see the evolution of search engine optimization and it will also guide you in the right direction to get better results.', '', '&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The work of SEO has actually evolved over time because of Google cracking spam techniques, the increase of mobile, changes within the SERPs so on. However what will SEO very do currently, and the way has this role modified over the years?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Just dwell in past and look at the present&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On-Page Optimization:&lt;/strong&gt; When executing on-page optimisation within the previous days, SEOs would map 2 to 5 keywords per URL and optimize the page parts (title, meta description, headings, body content, etc.) for these keywords.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;But things have modified. Now, with advances in linguistics search and machine learning, a page will rank for plenty of connected keywords, not simply the keywords that you optimize the page. This can be a stronger approach of doing things, as having content that fulfills the requirements of what users are searching for (rather than simply being the most effective match for a given keyword string) could be a higher expertise.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Device:&lt;/strong&gt; Back within the day, it absolutely was all regarding optimizing for desktops as a result of that was the first device accustomed surf online.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Today, mobile devices have immediately beco