(74, '22', 'All you want to know about Google Penguin 4.0', '0', 'all-you-want-to-know-about-google-penguin-4', 'Google finally rolled out its Penguin 4.0 algorithm update', '2016-10-03', '1475505802google 4.0.png', 'Google 4.0 Update', '', '', '&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px&quot;&gt;Google first launched the Penguin update in April 2012 to catch sites spamming the search results. Penguin is now part of Google&amp;rsquo;s core algorithm, penalizing websites that use various black-hat link schemes to manipulate search rankings. Now the penguin is back, as Google &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://webmasters.googleblog.com/2016/09/penguin-is-now-part-of-our-core.html&quot; style=&quot;text-decoration:none;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;announced&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px&quot;&gt; a major Penguin 4.0 update in all languages last Friday,September 23, 2016&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px&quot;&gt;Here are the key changes, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px&quot;&gt;Now &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Penguin 4.0 update&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; will work in real-time, Google says that it will no longer comment on future Penguin refreshes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px&quot;&gt;With this update, data is refreshed in real time, so changes will be visible much faster, typically taking effect shortly after we recrawl and reindex a page. So there is no need to wait for a long time for the next algorithm refresh to assess your link removals. Because of Penguin&amp;#39;s real-time nature, it will be increasingly difficult to identify whether ranking changes can be attributed to Penguin refreshes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px&quot;&gt;Penguin now devalues spam by adjusting ranking based on spam signals, rather than affecting ranking of the whole site. So any penalties will be delivered to a specific page rather than an entire domain, which seems much fairer in the long-term.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n', '2016-10-03 14:43:22'),
(75, '22', 'Facebook wants to give “Free Basic Internet” to US, reports.', '0', 'facebook-wants-to-give-free-basic-internet-to-us-reports', 'Facebook is in converses with US government authorities and wireless carriers about conveying its Free Basic services to a huge number of individuals in the US, The Washington Post reported', '2016-10-07', '1475846176Free_Basics_Facebook.png', 'Facebook Free Basic Internet', '', '', '&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px&quot;&gt;The Washington Post initially reported details of Facebook&amp;#39;s talks and it would like to dispatch an application known as Free Basics, referring to numerous individuals acquainted with the arrangement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Facebook&amp;#39;s &amp;#39;Free Basics&amp;#39; project&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; expects to give this availability to under-served and ruined groups, Facebook is examining its arrangements with U.S. authorities with the expectation that the venture will be seen positively by the legislature and can maintain a strategic distance from a rehash of what happened in India. Facebook has since changed Free Basics to incorporate all outsiders that desire to be incorporated, if they submit to an overseeing set of tenets, for example, not uploading HD video or photos that consume a lot of mobile data. The application would give access to news, data and well-being administrations. It&amp;#39;s not yet clear how far &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/rebelutedigital/&quot;&gt;Facebook&lt;/a&gt; has gotten with its endeavors, or what precisely the US rendition of Free Basics will offer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px&quot;&gt;It&amp;#39;s not yet clear how far Facebook has gotten with its endeavors, or what precisely the US rendition of Free Basics will offer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2016-10-07 13:16:16');
